#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clients-slemicro.adoc:20
msgid ""
"Following the bootstrapping process, automatic booting is disabled on "
"{micro} clients. This change was implemented due to intermittent automatic "
"reboots, which could occurr before {salt} could relay the results of "
"applying the bootstrap {salt} state."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clients-slemicro.adoc:21
msgid ""
"Although a reboot is automatically scheduled after registration is "
"completed, it is respecting the default reboot manager maintenance window.  "
"This window may be several hours after the client is registered.  It is "
"advisable to manually reboot the client after the registration script "
"finishes, to speed up the registration and to see the system appear in the "
"system list."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clients-slemicro.adoc:22
msgid ""
"When using a bootstrap script with {micro} systems, ensure that the "
"certificate section of the script has this content:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clients-slemicro.adoc:23
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clients-slmicro.adoc:18
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"ORG_CA_CERT=RHN-ORG-TRUSTED-SSL-CERT\n"
"ORG_CA_CERT_IS_RPM_YN=0\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clients-slemicro.adoc:24
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clients-slmicro.adoc:19
msgid ""
"Either edit the bootstrap script directly and add the settings, or create "
"the bootstrap script with these parameters:"
msgstr ""

#.  2023-12-12, ke: remains in /srv, see
#.  https://github.com/uyuni-project/uyuni-docs/pull/2682/files#r1423757456
#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clients-slemicro.adoc:25
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mgr-bootstrap --script=bootstrap-sle-micro.sh \\\n"
"    --ssl-cert=/srv/www/htdocs/pub/RHN-ORG-TRUSTED-SSL-CERT\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clients-slemicro.adoc:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "Reboot {micro}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clients-slemicro.adoc:27
msgid ""
"{micro} is a transactional system.  Transactional updates in general support "
"several reboot methods.  It is recommended to use [systemitem]``systemd`` "
"for rebooting in systems managed by {productname}.  Using other methods can "
"lead to undesired behavior."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clients-slemicro.adoc:28
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clients-slmicro.adoc:23
msgid ""
"When bootstrapping a transactional system on {productname}, "
"[systemitem]``systemd`` will be configured as the reboot method "
"([literal]``REBOOT_METHOD``), if the system is in its default "
"configuration.  Such a configuration allows {productname} to control the "
"reboot action, and rebooting can be performed immediately or scheduled with "
"{productname} as wanted."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clients-slemicro.adoc:30
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clients-slmicro.adoc:25
msgid ""
"By default, the reboot method during client installation is set to "
"[option]``auto``.  With the [option]``auto`` boot method, "
"[command]``rebootmgrd`` will be used to reboot the system according to the "
"configured policies if the service is running.  Policies can be to reboot "
"instantly or during a maintenance window.  For more information, see the "
"[command]``rebootmgrd``(8) man page.  Otherwise if [command]``rebootmgrd`` "
"is not running, {productname} will call [command]``systemctl reboot``."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clients-slemicro.adoc:31
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/clients-slmicro.adoc:26
msgid ""
"Using any method different from [command]``systemd`` may cause undesired "
"behavior."
msgstr ""

#.  2023-05-23, ke: The rest is commented and the user will not see the
#.                  following remarks/background info:
#. Otherwise, the only thing Suma will be able to do is to ask for a reboot and it will be managed in the peculiarities of each reboot method. Not having control of when the reboot should happen, also takes away from Suma the ability to perform the reboot on its own maintenance windows, which is not the ideal configuration.
#. The user must be able to change reboot method at any time and SUSE Manager will keep it. But in this case we should alert in the documentation that using any method different from systemd may cause undesired behavior.
