#. type: Title =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-default.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Default Contact Method ({salt})"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-default.adoc:2
msgid ""
"The default contact method using the {salt} protocol is recommended unless "
"there are specific needs.  For more information about {salt} in general, see "
"xref:specialized-guides:salt/salt-overview.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-default.adoc:3
msgid ""
"The {salt} Contact Method is the best scaling method.  All new {productname} "
"features are supported."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-default.adoc:4
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-intro.adoc:15
msgid ""
"The so-called traditional contact protocol is no longer supported with "
"{productname} 5.0 and later.  Before upgrading from {productname} 4 to 5, "
"any existing traditional clients including the traditional proxies must be "
"migrated to {salt} or replaced with {salt} proxies."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-default.adoc:5
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-intro.adoc:16
msgid ""
"For more information about migrating traditional {productname} 4 clients to "
"{salt} clients, see https://documentation.suse.com/suma/4.3/en/suse-manager/"
"client-configuration/contact-methods-migrate-traditional.html"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-default.adoc:6
msgid ""
"Software updates are generally pushed from the server to the client.  "
"Connections are initiated from the client.  This means you must open ports "
"on the server, not on clients.  The {salt} clients are also known as {salt} "
"minions.  {productname} Server installs a daemon on every client."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-default.adoc:7
msgid ""
"If you need to use {salt} clients in a disconnected setup you can configure "
"SSH Push as a contact method.  With this contact method, clients can be "
"located in a firewall-protected zone called a DMZ.  For more information "
"about SSH Push, see xref:client-configuration:contact-methods-saltssh.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-default.adoc:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "Onboarding Details"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-default.adoc:9
msgid ""
"{salt} has its own database to keep the keys for the minions. This needs to "
"be kept in sync with the {productname} database.  As soon as the key is "
"accepted in {salt}, the onboarding process in {productname} starts."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-default.adoc:10
msgid ""
"The onboarding process will look for existing systems in the {productname} "
"database by searching for the ``minion_id`` and the ``machine-id``.  "
"Depending on the outcome, the following scenarios are possible:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-default.adoc:11
msgid "If nothing is found, the new system gets created."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-default.adoc:12
msgid ""
"In case an entry with the ``minion_id`` or the ``machine-id`` is found, that "
"system will be migrated to match the new system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-default.adoc:13
msgid ""
"In case there is a match for both entries, and they are not the same system, "
"the onboarding will be aborted with an error."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-default.adoc:14
msgid ""
"In this case the administrator needs to resolve the conflict by removing at "
"least one of the systems."
msgstr ""

#
#. type: Title =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-intro.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Client Contact Methods"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-intro.adoc:2
msgid ""
"There are three contact methods how the {productname} Server can communicate "
"with clients.  They are based on {salt} protocols."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-intro.adoc:3
msgid ""
"Which {salt} contact method you use depends on the type of client, and your "
"network architecture:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-intro.adoc:4
#, no-wrap
msgid "Default (Salt)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-intro.adoc:5
msgid ""
"is the default choice and is recommended unless there are specific needs.  "
"For more information, see xref:client-configuration:contact-methods-default."
"adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-intro.adoc:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "SSH Push"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-intro.adoc:7
msgid ""
"is useful only if network restrictions make it impossible for clients to "
"establish contact to the server.  It is supported with the {salt} Bundle "
"only.  This contact method has serious limitations.  For more information, "
"see xref:client-configuration:contact-methods-saltssh.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-intro.adoc:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "SSH Push (with tunnel)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-intro.adoc:9
msgid ""
"is the same as SSH Push, but with using a secured communication tunnel.  For "
"more information, see xref:client-configuration:contact-methods-saltssh-"
"tunnel.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-intro.adoc:10
msgid "Implementation of {salt} communication software options:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-intro.adoc:11
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Salt Bundle"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-intro.adoc:12
msgid ""
"is a single binary package containing {salt} Minion, Python 3, required "
"Python modules, and libraries.  Thus the {salt} contact method is "
"independent from software installed on the client.  Using the {salt} Bundle "
"is the default.  It is the only supported implementation for the SSH Push or "
"SSH Push (with tunnel) contact method.  For more information, see xref:"
"client-configuration:contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-intro.adoc:13
#, no-wrap
msgid "Salt Minion"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-intro.adoc:14
msgid "is {salt} software installed on the client system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:2
#, no-wrap
msgid "What is Salt Bundle?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:3
msgid ""
"The Salt Bundle is a single binary package containing {salt} Minion, "
"Python 3, required Python modules, and libraries."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:4
msgid ""
"The Salt Bundle is shipped with Python 3 and all the requirements for {salt} "
"to run. Thus Salt Bundle does not use the Python version install on the "
"client as system software.  The Salt Bundle can be installed on clients that "
"do not meet the requirements for a given {salt} version."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:5
msgid ""
"It is also possible to use the Salt Bundle on systems that run a {salt} "
"Minion connected to a {salt} Master other than the {productname} {salt} "
"Master."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "Client Registration with Salt Bundle as a Minion"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:7
msgid ""
"The registration method with the Salt Bundle is the recommended registration "
"method.  This section explains the advantages and limitations of the current "
"implementation.  The Salt Bundle is provided as the [package]``venv-salt-"
"minion`` that consists of {salt}, Python 3, and the Python modules {salt} "
"depends on.  Bootstrapping with {webui} is using Salt Bundle as well, so "
"bootstrapping with {webui} is not Python dependant.  Using the Salt Bundle, "
"it is no longer needed that the client provides any Python interpreter or "
"modules."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:8
msgid ""
"If you bootstrap new clients, registration with the Salt Bundle is the "
"default method.  You can switch existing clients to the Salt Bundle method.  "
"If you switch, the [package]``salt-minion`` package and its dependencies "
"will stay installed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using the {salt} Bundle with the {salt} Minion"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:10
msgid ""
"The {salt} Bundle can be used with the {salt} Minion managed by the {salt} "
"Master other than {productname} Server at the same time.  If the Salt Bundle "
"is installed on a client {productname} Server will manage the configuration "
"files of the Salt Bundle, the configuration files of [literal]``salt-"
"minion`` will not be managed in this case.  For more information, see xref:"
"client-configuration:registration-cli.adoc#_salt_bundle_configuration[Salt "
"Bundle configuration]."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:11
msgid ""
"To bootstrap a client with the {salt} Minion managed by the {salt} Master "
"other than {productname} Server it is recommended to use [command]``mgr-"
"bootstrap`` [option]``--force-bundle`` when generating the bootstrap script, "
"or to set [option]``FORCE_VENV_SALT_MINION`` to `1` in the bootstrap script."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:12
msgid ""
"For bootstrapping with {webui} [literal]``mgr_force_venv_salt_minion`` set "
"to [literal]``true`` pillar can be specified globally.  For more "
"information, see xref:specialized-guides:salt/salt-states-and-pillars.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:13
#, no-wrap
msgid "Switching from {salt} Minion to Salt Bundle"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:14
msgid ""
"The {salt} state [literal]``util.mgr_switch_to_venv_minion`` is available to "
"switch from [package]``salt-minion`` to [package]``venv-salt-minion``.  It "
"is recommended to switch to [package]``venv-salt-minion`` in two steps to "
"avoid trouble with shifting processes:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:15
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Switching with [literal]``util.mgr_switch_to_venv_minion`` state to [package]``venv-salt-minion``"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:16
msgid ""
"Apply [literal]``util.mgr_switch_to_venv_minion`` with no pillar specified "
"first.  This will result in the switch to [package]``venv-salt-minion`` with "
"copying configuration files etc.  It will not clean up the original "
"[package]``salt-minion`` configurations and its packages."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "salt <minion_id> state.apply util.mgr_switch_to_venv_minion\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:18
msgid ""
"Apply [literal]``util.mgr_switch_to_venv_minion`` with "
"[literal]``mgr_purge_non_venv_salt`` set to [literal]``True`` to remove "
"[package]``salt-minion`` and with [literal]``mgr_purge_non_venv_salt_files`` "
"set to [literal]``True`` to remove all the files related to [package]``salt-"
"minion``.  This second step ensures the first step was processed, and then "
"removes the old configuration files and the now obsolete [package]``salt-"
"minion`` package."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:19
#, no-wrap
msgid "salt <minion_id> state.apply util.mgr_switch_to_venv_minion pillar='{\"mgr_purge_non_venv_salt_files\": True, \"mgr_purge_non_venv_salt\": True}'\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:20
msgid ""
"In case of running the second step of switching with skipping the first "
"step, state apply process could fail as it requires stopping the "
"[systemitem]``salt-minion`` which is used to execute the command on the "
"client side."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:21
msgid ""
"On the other hand, it is also possible to avoid installing the Salt Bundle "
"and keep using [package]``salt-minion`` instead.  In this case, specify one "
"of these options:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:22
msgid "Execute [command]``mgr-bootstrap`` with [option]``--no-bundle`` option."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:23
msgid ""
"Set [literal]``AVOID_VENV_SALT_MINION`` to [literal]``1`` in the generated "
"bootstrap script."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:24
msgid ""
"For bootstrap state set the [literal]``mgr_avoid_venv_salt_minion`` pillar "
"to [literal]``True``."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:25
#, no-wrap
msgid "SSH Push with the Salt Bundle"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:26
msgid ""
"The Salt Bundle is also used when performing SSH Push actions to clients."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:27
msgid ""
"A shell script deploys the Salt Bundle onto the target system without "
"installing [package]``venv-salt-minion`` before any {salt} command is "
"executed. Because the Salt Bundle contains the whole {salt} code base, no "
"[literal]``salt-thin`` is deployed.  SSH Push (including bootstrapping using "
"the {webui}) uses the Python 3 interpreter within the bundle.  The target "
"system does not need to have any other Python interpreter installed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:28
msgid ""
"The Python 3 deployed with the Bundle is used to handle SSH Push session on "
"the client, so SSH Push (including bootstrapping with {webui}) is not "
"dependant on Python installed on the system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:29
msgid ""
"Using `salt-thin` can be enabled as a fallback method, but it requires "
"Python 3 to be installed on the client.  This method is not recommended nor "
"supported and exists for development purposes only.  Set [option]``web."
"ssh_use_salt_thin`` to `true` in the [path]``/etc/rhn/rhn.conf`` "
"configuration file."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:30
msgid ""
"The bootstrap repository must be created before bootstrapping the client "
"with {webui}.  SSH Push is using the Salt Bundle taken from the bootstrap "
"repository based on the detected target operating system.  For more "
"information, see xref:client-configuration:bootstrap-repository."
"adoc#_prepare_to_create_a_bootstrap_repository[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:31
msgid ""
"SSH Push is using [path]``/var/tmp`` to deploy Salt Bundle to and execute "
"{salt} commands on the client with the bundled Python.  Therefore you must "
"not mount [path]``/var/tmp`` with the [option]``noexec`` option.  It is not "
"possible to bootstrap the clients, which have [path]``/var/tmp`` mounted "
"with [option]``noexec`` option, with the {webui} because the bootstrap "
"process is using SSH Push to reach a client."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "Extend Salt Bundle with Python packages using pip"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:33
msgid ""
"The Salt Bundle includes [literal]``pip`` to make it possible to extend the "
"functionality of the bundled {salt} Minion with extra Python packages."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:34
msgid ""
"By default, [command]``salt <minion_id> pip.install <package-name>`` "
"installs the Python package specified by [literal]``<package_name>`` into "
"[path]``/var/lib/venv-salt-minion/local``."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:35
msgid ""
"If needed, the path [path]``/var/lib/venv-salt-minion/local`` can be "
"overridden by setting the [literal]``VENV_PIP_TARGET`` environment variable "
"for the [literal]``venv-salt-minion.service``.  It is recommended to use a "
"systemd drop-in configuration file for the service.  It could be done with "
"the configuration file [path]``/etc/systemd/system/venv-salt-minion.service."
"d/10-pip-destination.conf``:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:36
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[Service]\n"
"Environment=VENV_PIP_TARGET=/new/path/local/venv-salt-minion/pip\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltbundle.adoc:37
msgid ""
"The Python packages installed through [literal]``pip`` are not changing on "
"updating the Salt Bundle.  To ensure that such packages are available and "
"functional after an update, it is recommended to install them with a {salt} "
"state that is applied after Salt Bundle updates."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh-tunnel.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "SSH Push (With Tunnel) Contact Method"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh-tunnel.adoc:2
msgid ""
"SSH Push (with tunnel) ([literal]``ssh-push-tunnel``) is used in "
"environments where clients cannot reach the {productname} Server directly.  "
"In this environment, clients are located in a firewall-protected zone called "
"a DMZ.  No system within the DMZ is authorized to open a connection to the "
"internal network, including the {productname} Server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh-tunnel.adoc:3
msgid ""
"This SSH method creates an encrypted tunnel from the {productname} Server on "
"the internal network to the clients located on the DMZ.  After all actions "
"and events are executed, the tunnel is closed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh-tunnel.adoc:4
msgid ""
"The server uses SSH to contact the clients at regular intervals, checking in "
"and performing scheduled actions and events."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh-tunnel.adoc:5
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh.adoc:6
msgid ""
"Re-installing systems using the provisioning model is not currently "
"supported on clients managed with SSH Push."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/contact-methods-saltssh-tunnel.adoc:6
msgid ""
"The tunnel is used to provide the access to the server through the encrypted "
